        "content": "for the degree of Bachelor of Science Major in Speech & Hearing Science"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Graduation Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required for graduation: 120 hours."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "All students must complete a series of SHS professional core classes and an additional 12 credits of SHS electives.  Students are advised to work with the undergraduate academic advisor to ensure courses are taken in proper sequential order and, if desired, that they meet the requirements for eventual ASHA certification.   NOTE: For those planning on pursuing graduate studies in Speech-Language Pathology or Audiology, many graduate programs require 25 clinical observation hours prior to starting graduate school.  Some of these may be completed as part of SHS 475."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "University Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum of 40 hours of upper-division coursework, generally at the 300 and 400 level. These hours can be drawn from all elements of the degree. Students should consult their academic advisor for additional guidance in fulfilling this requirement."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "The university and residency requirements can be found in the Student Code (§ 3-801) and in the Academic Catalog."
      },
